CAPE TOWN, October 15 – Two suspects are expected to appear in the New Hanover Magistrate’s Court on Monday morning to face charges of illegal possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. In a statement, KwaZulu Natal police said the suspects,aged, 36 and 46, were arrested over the weekend during operations in the Mvoti area. “On Friday night, a joint intelligence driven operation was conducted by the Pietermaritzburg Tactical Response Team and Dalton SAPS targeting illegal firearms at Mvoti and Inadi location,” said police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala. “During the operation police officers swooped on two homesteads. One suspect was found in possession of a pistol and a rifle as well as ammunition. The second suspect was found at another homestead with three rifles and ammunition.” Gwala added that police also found a shotgun which could not be linked to anyone for now. Both suspects were arrested and charged for being in possession of illegal firearms and ammunition. – African News Agency (ANA)